14 Section 2. Section 72-17-302, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "72-17-302. Sale or purchase of parts and whole bodies prohibited. (1) A person may not
16 knowingly, for valuable consideration,:
17 (a) purchase or sell a part for:
18 (i) transplantation or therapy, if removal of the part is intended to occur after the death of the
19 decedent; or
20 (ii) research, education, or the training of search and rescue canines; or
21 (b) purchase or sell a whole body for transplantation, therapy, research, education, or the training
22 of search and rescue canines.
23 (2) Valuable consideration does not include reasonable payment for the removal, processing,
24 disposal, preservation, quality control, storage, or transportation of a part or a whole body, or for the
25 implantation of a part.
26 (3) A person who violates this section is guilty of a felony and upon on conviction is subject to a
27 fine not exceeding $50,000 or imprisonment not exceeding 5 years, or both."
